are all illegal in the vast majority of the country, and the letter of the law states that simple possession may mean years in jail. however, in some states (notably uttar pradesh, bihar, rajasthan, madhya pradesh, uttarakhand and orissa) the one legal and socially accepted way to consume cannabis is as bhang, a low-grade preparation sold at government-licensed shops that is not only smoked, but also made into cookies, chocolate and the infamous bhang lassi, a herb-laced version of the normally innocuous yogurt drink. bhang lassi is usually available at varying strengths, so use caution if opting for the stronger 